{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":125110,"duration_api_ms":124252,"num_turns":25,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"bcf2aa65-6d78-4e47-b419-a19c14d4af6a","total_cost_usd":0.89651925,"usage":{"input_tokens":16,"cache_creation_input_tokens":60741,"cache_read_input_tokens":835516,"output_tokens":3962,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":60741,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":16,"outputTokens":3962,"cacheReadInputTokens":835516,"cacheCreationInputTokens":60741,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.89651925,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 65 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures)","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes with no warnings","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","model.rs: TaskRunEntry has all required fields — milestone_id (line 275), bead_id (278), project_id (280), run_id (282), plan_hash (285), outcome (288), outcome_detail (290), started_at (293), finished_at (296) — all new optional fields use serde(default, skip_serializing_if) for backward compatibility","model.rs: MilestoneProgress now has skipped_beads counter (line 203) with serde(default) for backward compat, and remaining() accounts for it (line 213)","model.rs: MilestoneEventType::BeadSkipped variant added (line 240)","service.rs: record_bead_completion (line 329) now delegates entirely to update_task_run (line 344-357) — no second append, single completion path","service.rs: update_task_run (line 390) accepts snapshot_store, journal_store, and lineage_store; validates outcome is terminal (line 404-410); updates lineage via adapter; then mutates snapshot counters (lines 424-442) with correct Succeeded/Failed/Skipped handling; clears active_bead (443-449); and emits the appropriate journal event type (BeadCompleted/BeadFailed/BeadSkipped)","fs.rs: update_task_run (line 2344) uses AdvisoryFileLock (line 2357) via flock for the read-modify-write cycle, same lock used by append_task_run (line 2339)","fs.rs: update_task_run matching logic (lines 2387-2469) uses run_id when provided for exact match (line 2401-2446), falls back to open-match disambiguation when run_id is None, and rejects ambiguous matches with descriptive errors","fs.rs: update_task_run rejects already-finalized entries (lines 2472-2480), preventing duplicate terminal updates","Test: update_task_run_modifies_outcome verifies snapshot counters, active_bead, run_id backfill, plan_hash, journal event after update","Test: skipped_runs_are_tracked_without_counting_as_failures verifies skipped_beads=1, failed_beads=0, BeadSkipped journal event","Test: completion_flow_rejects_duplicate_finalization verifies already-finalized error","Test: lineage_updates_require_run_id_when_multiple_open_attempts_exist verifies ambiguity rejection and exact run_id matching","Test: multiple_retries_visible_for_same_bead verifies 2 entries with distinct outcomes after start→fail→start→succeed cycle","Test: bead_start_and_completion_tracking verifies end-to-end flow including runs.len()==1 (no duplicate append)","Test: task_run_entry_backward_compat_without_new_fields verifies old JSON without new fields deserializes correctly","Test: find_runs_for_bead_filters_correctly verifies chronological filtering and empty results for unknown beads"],"findings_or_gaps":["Outstanding risk acknowledged by implementor: task-run completion spans lineage, snapshot, and journal writes without a cross-file transaction; a crash between writes could leave artifacts temporarily inconsistent. This is acceptable given the file-based storage model and the advisory locking already in place — a future repair/recovery mechanism could address this if needed.","The non-terminal outcome guard in update_task_run uses AppError::RunStartFailed (line 405-409) which is semantically misleading for a finalization rejection — a more specific error variant like RunFinalizeFailed would be clearer, but this is a minor naming concern, not a correctness issue.","find_runs_for_bead sorts by started_at then finished_at (lines 2511-2514), which is correct for chronological ordering but does not acquire the advisory lock during reads. This is acceptable since reads don't need mutual exclusion for correctness in single-writer scenarios, but worth noting for future multi-writer considerations."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"3f31e0a2-e3a9-4cb1-bd44-d7271d52d40c"}
